The FCT Police Command has arrested one Oputa Vitus in connection with the murder of staff of the Abuja Electrical Distribution Company (AEDC). The deceased was attacked and stabbed with a knife by the suspect at Pasali, Kabusa on Tuesday. DSP Anjuguri Manzah, Police Public Relations Officer, made the announcement in a statement on Wednesday. He said the arrest followed a distress call received at Kabusa Division that the suspect inflicted serious injuries on two AEDC workers. The staff had been deployed to the community on official assignment. The statement confirmed that the knife has been recovered as an exhibit. “As a result of the incident, one Ibrahim Garba Haji ‘m’ 50 years old, a staff of AEDC, who was stabbed on the chest, was certified dead at the hospital where he was rushed to for medical attention. “Meanwhile, the second victim is still on hospital admission”, it added. The Command said investigation into the incident has commenced and that the suspect would be arraigned in court upon the conclusion. These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More BREAKING: AEDC official stabbed to death while disconnecting light, one other injured Nigerian Newspapers: 10 things you need to know this Wednesday morning First Bank Mpape robbery: Police set to arraign staff, robbers